What is Ajax and how it works?

Ajax, How It Works and How To Use It. Ajax is written with JavaScript using specialized functions with the ability to connect to the server. The code that connects to the server and accepts its response is sometimes referred to as an Ajax engine. An Ajax engine is provided with a URL and, optionally, data to send to the server.
